Option (C) is incorrect because the ball is not being influenced by a force in the northward direction. The correct answer is (D) Move nowhere.

In this case, the ball is being acted upon by equal forces from opposite directions (east and west), which means the forces will cancel each other out and the ball will not move in any direction. Therefore, the correct answer is (D) Move nowhere. Options (A), (B), and (C) are not accurate because the ball is not being pushed in any specific direction.
